                                                </span><span
                                                    style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;">
                                                    <p style="line-height: 150%" class="MsoNormal" align="justify"><span
                                                            style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;">Currently
                                                            250,000 hectares of rainforest is slashed and burned each
                                                            year in </span><span
                                                            style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;">Peru</span><span
                                                            style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;">.
                                                            Whilst one aim of the programme is reforestation, there is
                                                            an urgent need to educate an impoverished indigenous
                                                            population to protect their environment and to also provide
                                                            them with alternative, sustainable low-impact employment so
                                                            that they no longer need to cut down valuable trees for a
                                                            living. </span><span
                                                            style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;"><a
                                                                href="/save-the-rainforest"
